{
  "stem": "27335.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was-- there was-- there was an agent who was waiting-- was waiting-- was in Winnipeg, a Joseph Swartz.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was-- he was a settler, sort of doing-- working for the CPR.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then he then led us out to-- out to Edmonton.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then-- then he landed us-- handed us, the whole family, over to a CPR agent.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then they took us southwest, for 40-- 40 miles, southwest from Edmonton, where the CPR-- I don't know if you know the history of Canada.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When the CPR built the railways, by agreement with the Canadian-- Canadian government, they inject a wee bit of-- of sod.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] The, uh, state, uh, reserves so much land along the railway tracks, some-- in some places, 10-- 10 miles on in each way.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And where the CPR built a railroad-- through like-- like in the prairies, I think that it's five or six miles on both-- both sides of the railway.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That was then donated by the Canadian government to the CPR.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It's-- when it then, it aligned, lead into the-- into the Rocky Mountains-- there's a different story, again.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But there, too, they-- they had certain rights, through the CPR.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So that's a-- that's how it work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And on this land, it was-- you know, the whole-- the whole prairie-- Canada was divided up to-- up to this, uh, uh, uh, sections.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the quarter section was 160 acres-- that was the smallest.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it was-- it was forest-- that you could-- you couldn't see see the God from it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And thus we started to-- to-- work on it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Cut the-- cut the trees, and what.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But-- but-- then we leave it soon.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
